Execution:
1. For the peer that listens and accepts a chat request:
	./peer <PORT on which server listens>

2. For the peer that starts a server and sends a chat request:
	./peer <PORT on which its server runs> <IP to connect to> <PORT to connect to>


Features:
1. Half-duplex messaging.
2. File transfer using both TCP and UDP.
3. Progress bar showing progress of both sending and receiving on either side.